==Controversies==
During the draw on 13 December 2024, when [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] was drawn, the map of the country did not include the disputed area of [[Crimea]], which led to outrage from the [[Ukrainian Association of Football]]. FIFA later apologised for the incident.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/clyj333j9yvo |title=Fifa regrets Ukraine map error at 2026 World Cup qualifiers draw |publisher=BBC Sport |website=bbc.com |date=17 December 2024 |access-date=27 December 2024}}</ref>

In [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group I|Group I]], the [[Norwegian Football Federation]] stated that they "cannot remain indifferent to [[Gaza genocide|Israel's disproportionate attacks on the civilian population in Gaza]]"  during the [[Gaza war]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2024-12-15/ty-article/.premium/cant-remain-indifferent-norway-highlights-gaza-ahead-of-world-cup-match-against-israel/00000193-ca3c-d432-a193-eafdfa9f0000 |title='Can't Remain Indifferent': Norway Spotlights Gaza Ahead of World Cup Qualifier Against Israel |publisher=Haaretz |website=haaretz.com |date=15 December 2024 |access-date=27 December 2024}}</ref> In the same group, during the [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]]–[[Israel national football team|Israel]] qualification match, Estonian fans waved a banner targeting Israeli captain [[Eli Dasa]] who played for Russian club [[FC Dynamo Moscow]] from 2022 to 2025, for comments Dasa made that he was "proud to play" in Russia. The banner was removed at the request of UEFA.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zenziper |first1=Nadav |title=Estonian police seek to question Israeli soccer captain over pro-Russia remarks |url=https://www.ynetnews.com/culture/article/b1gafcz7ll |website=Ynetnews |language=en |date=7 June 2025}}</ref> Also in the same group, the Italian Football Coaches' Association called for Israel to be suspended prior to the [[Italy national football team|Italy]]–Israel qualification match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/italian-soccer-coaches-call-israel-125723398.html|title=Italian soccer coaches call for Israel to be suspended by UEFA and FIFA over Gaza war|first=DANIELLA|last=MATAR|date=August 20, 2025|website=Yahoo Sports}}</ref>

Following the end of qualification, some UEFA members complained that Europe's allocation of 16 places was insufficient. They also criticised the home advantage which some nations had had in the play-offs, believing that the games should have been hosted on neutral grounds.<ref>{{cite news |last=Delaney |first=Miguel |date=1 April 2026 |title=European countries fume over home advantage in 'extremely unfair' World Cup qualifying |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup-qualifying-uefa-europe-b2949908.html |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=3 April 2026}}</ref>

